The paper discusses unsupervised learning algorithms for neural networks applied to image classification, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of support vector machines (SVMs) for classification, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of a nonnegative classical multidimensional scaling cost-function, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
